<H1>The Risks Digest Volume 16: Issue 78</H1>
<H2> Thursday 2 February 1995 </H2>
<H3>Forum on Risks to the Public in Computers and Related Systems</H3>
<I><A HREF="http://www.acm.org">ACM</A>
Committee on Computers and Public Policy, Peter G. Neumann, moderator</I><P>
<H2>Contents</H2><DL>
<DT><IMG SRC="/Images/redball.gif" ALT="o" WIDTH="14" HEIGHT="14">
<A HREF="#subj1">Novel form of interference </A>
<DD>
<A HREF="#subj1.1">Mich Kabay</A><BR>
<DT><IMG SRC="/Images/redball.gif" ALT="o" WIDTH="14" HEIGHT="14">
<A HREF="#subj2">Attack on glasfibre cables causes Lufthansa delays </A>
<DD>
<A HREF="#subj2.1">Klaus Brunnstein</A><BR>
<DT><IMG SRC="/Images/redball.gif" ALT="o" WIDTH="14" HEIGHT="14">
<A HREF="#subj3">Anonymous ?? Survey </A>
<DD>
<A HREF="#subj3.1">Dave Moore</A><BR>
<DT><IMG SRC="/Images/redball.gif" ALT="o" WIDTH="14" HEIGHT="14">
<A HREF="#subj4">Deep Faults with NYNEX default? </A>
<DD>
<A HREF="#subj4.1">Edward P Ravin</A><BR>
<DT><IMG SRC="/Images/redball.gif" ALT="o" WIDTH="14" HEIGHT="14">
<A HREF="#subj5">Nynex glitch lets Call ID work even if blocked </A>
