<H1>The Risks Digest Volume 16: Issue 93</H1>
<H2> Monday 20 March 1995 </H2>
<H3>Forum on Risks to the Public in Computers and Related Systems</H3>
<I><A HREF="http://www.acm.org">ACM</A>
Committee on Computers and Public Policy, Peter G. Neumann, moderator</I><P>
<H2>Contents</H2><DL>
<DT><IMG SRC="/Images/redball.gif" ALT="o" WIDTH="14" HEIGHT="14">
<A HREF="#subj1">About the "Altona Railway software glitch" </A>
<DD>
<A HREF="#subj1.1">Klaus Brunnstein</A><BR>
<DT><IMG SRC="/Images/redball.gif" ALT="o" WIDTH="14" HEIGHT="14">
<A HREF="#subj2">Credit-Card Fraud </A>
<DD>
<A HREF="#subj2.1">NYT via Edupage</A><BR>
<DT><IMG SRC="/Images/redball.gif" ALT="o" WIDTH="14" HEIGHT="14">
<A HREF="#subj3">Keeping buses on time plus a little eavesdropping </A>
<DD>
<A HREF="#subj3.1">Mark Kruse</A><BR>
