<H1>The Risks Digest Volume 17: Issue 25</H1>
<H2>Friday 11 August 1995</H2>
<H3>Forum on Risks to the Public in Computers and Related Systems</H3>
<I><A HREF="http://www.acm.org">ACM</A>
Committee on Computers and Public Policy,
<A HREF="http://www.csl.sri.com/neumann/neumann.html">Peter G.
Neumann</A>, moderator</I><P>
<H2>Contents</H2><DL>
<DT><IMG SRC="/Images/redball.gif" ALT="o" WIDTH="14" HEIGHT="14">
<A HREF="#subj1">"Computer" gets exam results wrong:  Rounding error</A>
<DD><A HREF="#subj1.1">Donald Mackie</A><BR>
<DT><IMG SRC="/Images/redball.gif" ALT="o" WIDTH="14" HEIGHT="14">
<A HREF="#subj2">The Royal Majesty revisited</A>
<DD><A HREF="#subj2.1">Bob Frankston</A><BR>
<DT><IMG SRC="/Images/redball.gif" ALT="o" WIDTH="14" HEIGHT="14">
<A HREF="#subj3">Re: An unusual off-by-one error</A>
<DD><A HREF="#subj3.1">William R. Ward</A><BR>
