<I>11 Aug 1995 01:48:16 GMT</I>
<P>)
) I emailed the list's maintainer, Alex Lopez-Ortiz, to point out what I<BR>
) assumed was a typo.  He replied to say that actually the error was the<BR>
) result of a bug -- he had used a program to remove LaTeX math formatting<BR>
) codes from an online copy of the paragraph, and it had apparently shifted<BR>
) each formula by one position in the text!
<P>
This is particularly interesting, because the book has as one of its
co-authors Donald Knuth, whom as we all know was the originator of TeX, from
which LaTeX is derived.  Perhaps the program was getting back at its author
in some way?
